      },
      "lineNbr": 144,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T07:57:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/2107340/2/milo/frontend/resultui/src/models/test_node.ts#152 you said that there is a benefit of checking nextSeg !\u003d\u003d undefined. I did not understand that. \nnextSeg can be undefined iff test.idSegs is empty. In particular, a valid segment is always a string.\nso I still think the code would be cleaner if we did\n\n  if (test.idSegs.length \u003d\u003d 0) {\n    this.tests.push(test.test);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const nextSeg \u003d test.idSegs.pop();",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 144,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 144,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "26661e6e3e1841ba52dc2fe7ec9ee6d6d5a2a467",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "76dfa415_37b15aad",
        "filename": "milo/frontend/resultui/src/models/test_node.ts",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 144,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T16:01:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the return type of test.idSegs.pop() is string | undefined.\nSo if we check length,\nthe code would be\n```\nif (test.idSegs.length \u003d\u003d 0) {\n  this.tests.push(test.test);\n  return;\n}\nconst nextSeg \u003d test.idSegs.pop() as string;\n```\nWe need to cast string | undefined to string.\nI want to limit the usage of down casting as much as possible.\nI do agree that the gain is very marginal though.",
      "parentUuid": "e86394b6_e131b031",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 144,
        "startChar": 4,
